{"id":2281,"date":"2021-07-22T23:22:39","date_gmt":"2021-07-22T23:22:39","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/?page_id=2281"},"modified":"2021-08-23T21:20:42","modified_gmt":"2021-08-23T21:20:42","slug":"intracerebral-hemorrhage","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/intracerebral-hemorrhage\/","title":{"rendered":"Intracerebral Hemorrhage"},"content":{"rendered":"\t\t<div data-elementor-type=\"wp-page\" data-elementor-id=\"2281\" class=\"elementor elementor-2281\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-section-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-237806f elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"237806f\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-24d83c2\" data-id=\"24d83c2\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-8178bf5 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"8178bf5\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h1 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Neurosurgery: Intracerebral Hemorrhage (ICH)<\/h1>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-3fb9b3c elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"3fb9b3c\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-cc88e83\" data-id=\"cc88e83\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-8fa06ee elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"8fa06ee\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Intracerebral Hemorrhage (ICH)<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-c991400 elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"c991400\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-b748f33\" data-id=\"b748f33\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-e878a96 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"e878a96\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><strong>Definitions<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Intracerebral Hemorrhage (ICH): Bleeding within the Brain Parenchyma<\/li><li>Types:<ul><li><em>Spontaneous Intracerebral Hemorrhage<\/em><\/li><li><em>Traumatic Intracerebral Hemorrhage<\/em><ul><li><a href=\"http:\/\/operativereview.com\/traumatic-brain-injury\/\">*See Trauma: Traumatic Brain Injury (TBI)<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Second Most Common Cause of Stroke (Behind Ischemic Stroke)<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Causes<\/strong><\/p><ul><li><em>Hypertensive Vasculopathy<\/em> \u2013 Most Common Cause of Spontaneous ICH<ul><li>Hemorrhaging Vessels Often Occur at Right Angles \u2013 No Protection from Gradual Decrease in Vessel Caliber Size<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li><em>Cerebral Amyloid Angiopathy<\/em><\/li><li><em>Ruptured Saccular Aneurysm<\/em><ul><li>Occurs at Branching Points<\/li><li>Most Common Site: <strong>Anterior Communicating Artery<\/strong><\/li><li>Rupture Mortality Rate: 50%<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li><em>Arteriovenous Malformation (AVM)<\/em> \u2013 Most Common Cause in Peds<\/li><li>Less Common Causes:<ul><li>Septic Embolism<\/li><li>Cerebral Venous Thrombosis<\/li><li>Brain Tumor<\/li><li>Cerebral Hyperperfusion Syndrome<\/li><li>Drug Abuse<\/li><li>Bleeding Diathesis<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Presentation<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Symptoms Often Progress Over Minutes-Hours<ul><li>*Compared to Sudden Onset of Maximal Intensity with Embolism or Subarachnoid Hemorrhage<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Altered Mental Status<\/li><li>Headache<\/li><li>Nausea &amp; Vomiting<\/li><li>Seizures<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Diagnosis<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Primary Diagnosis: Imaging (CT or MRI)<\/li><li>May Need CTA\/MRA to Determine Etiology Such as AVM or Aneurysm<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Treatment<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Definitive Management Depends on Pathology, Performance Status &amp; Prognosis<\/li><li>Potential Managements:<ul><li>Surgical Resection<\/li><li>Coil Embolization<\/li><li>Anticoagulant Reversal<\/li><li>Antihypertensives<\/li><li>Antiepileptic Treatment<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Intracranial Pressure Management<ul><li><a href=\"http:\/\/operativereview.com\/traumatic-brain-injury\/\">*See Trauma: Traumatic Brain Injury (TBI)<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Neurosurgery: Intracerebral Hemorrhage (ICH) Intracerebral Hemorrhage (ICH) Definitions Intracerebral Hemorrhage (ICH): Bleeding within the Brain Parenchyma Types: Spontaneous Intracerebral Hemorrhage Traumatic Intracerebral Hemorrhage *See Trauma: Traumatic Brain Injury (TBI) Second Most Common Cause of Stroke (Behind Ischemic Stroke) Causes Hypertensive Vasculopathy \u2013 Most Common Cause of Spontaneous ICH Hemorrhaging Vessels Often Occur at Right Angles [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"_mi_skip_tracking":false},"folder":[28],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/2281"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=2281"}],"version-history